---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="HueForge - Design System from One Color" description="One HEX, full design system. 40+ tokens, light + dark mode, WCAG auto-fix. Free.">
  <div class="pt-24 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
      <a href="/en/apps" class="text-sm text-text-muted hover:text-accent-purple transition-colors">&larr; All apps</a>

      <div class="flex items-center gap-6 mt-8 mb-12">
        <img src="/apps/huecraft-icon.png" alt="HueForge icon" width="128" height="128" class="rounded-[28px] shadow-lg" />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-3"><span class="gradient-text">HueForge</span></h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-text-muted">Design System from One Color</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Screenshots -->
      <div class="mb-12 overflow-x-auto">
        <div class="flex gap-4 pb-4" style="min-width: max-content;">
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_1.png" alt="Color palette" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_2.png" alt="Design tokens" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_3.png" alt="Brand kit" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_4.png" alt="Light mode" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_5.png" alt="Dark mode" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_6.png" alt="Export" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
          <img src="/apps/huecraft/screenshots/en/screenshot_7.png" alt="OKLCH sliders" class="h-[500px] rounded-2xl shadow-lg" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card-hover p-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card mb-8">
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          One color in. Full design system out. Enter a single HEX color and get a complete palette: 11-shade primary scale, neutral scale, semantic tokens, light mode, dark mode — all WCAG-checked. One tap fixes every contrast issue. Copy CSS, Swift, Tailwind, or JSON and paste straight into your project.
        </p>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          No account. No internet. No designer. Production-ready in 10 seconds.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">What HueForge Does</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted mb-6">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Export Palettes</strong> — copy your color harmony as CSS variables, Swift extensions, or Tailwind config. WCAG contrast matrix included</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">40+ Design Tokens</strong> — primary scale, neutral scale, semantic tokens from one brand color</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">OKLCH-Based Palette</strong> — perceptually uniform, not washed-out HSL</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Light + Dark Mode</strong> — both themes from one source color, split-view comparison</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">WCAG Auto-Fix</strong> — contrast checker with AA/AAA badges, one-tap fix for accessibility</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Code Export</strong> — CSS Custom Properties, SwiftUI Colors, Tailwind Config, JSON Tokens</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Semantic Tokens</strong> — background, surface, text, primary, border, ring, error, success</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-accent-green mt-1">&#10003;</span>
            <span><strong class="text-white">Palette Share Card</strong> — share your color palette as a visual card. Perfect for client presentations, Dribbble, and design chats</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Who It's For</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Indie hackers, solo devs, freelancers, startup founders — anyone shipping a product without a designer. If you've ever spent 2 hours picking colors and building dark mode by hand, HueForge replaces that with 10 seconds.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">vs. The Alternatives</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          Coolors: 5 random color strips, no dark mode, no WCAG, no code export. ColorSlurp: $4.99 freemium, no design system. Pastel: $3.99, no dark mode generation. HueForge: Free. Full system. Dark mode. WCAG. Code. Done.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-hover p-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Coming to App Store</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted">HueForge is preparing for release. Free for iOS.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-hover p-8 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-card mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Privacy</h2>
        <p class="text-text-muted mb-3">All data on device. No server, no cloud, no analytics.</p>
        <a href="/apps/huecraft/privacy" class="text-sm text-accent-purple hover:underline">Privacy Policy &rarr;</a>
      </div>

      <div class="text-sm text-text-muted">
        <p>Questions or feedback: <a href="mailto:magic4e@gmail.com" class="text-accent-purple hover:underline">magic4e@gmail.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
